text_entries.result: Offenders Exposed has been exposing domestic violence offenders, child abusers and sex offenders for 7 years. We keep getting shut down but that doesn’t stop us, here we go with our third attempt at keeping you up to date.

7/5/22
I have seen comments from a few people who have complained about the $2 per month subscription to access the website.

I would like those people to consider this, personally I have spent 8 years gathering the offenders to add to the website while exposing them on social media. Today, 7hrs were spent putting the details of 36 offenders into a spreadsheet to be sent off and added to the website. Every offender has to be double checked or I have to locate the sentencing details of each offender.

Personally, I have spent thousands of dollars over the past 8 years to subscribe to media so I can provide the info for free on social media.

I also have to maintain internet so I can access media sources.

I teamed up with someone last year who has spent $10,000 putting the site together, after my initial payment to him - there are also hosting fees to be paid for each month.

The website was put together as a first in this country that exposes not only sex offenders but domestic violence offenders and child abusers. When you consider the content, is $2 per month too much to ask to keep this project going while giving you a tool to screen people and keep your family safe?

We have done something to help the public stay aware, this is something the government should have done years ago but have failed to do.

Thank you to the people who have subscribed, your support is greatly appreciated

Tania

www.offendersexposed.com.au
Stay aware; stay safe. Australia’s first search engine for Sex Offenders, Domestic Violence Offenders and Child Abusers.

NARARA, NSW
PAUL ROBERT BAMFORTH, 50

21/9/22: Paul Robert Bamforth, 50, and Julia Ann Bamforth, 49,  lured a young boy with “free drugs” to their Narara home and filmed themselves sexually assaulting him over a five-year period.

Bamford pleaded guilty to 65 charges including 21 counts of aggravated sexual intercourse and will face Gosford District Court on September 29 to set a date to be sentenced.

Source: https://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/newslocal/central-coast/narara-couple-paul-robert-bamforth-and-julia-ann-bamforth-plead-guilty-to-child-sex-abuse/news-story/56c2e87ba214ffd6f149d390f3af0cb7

body.text:
11/4/22
PAKENHAM, VIC
CHRISTOPHER ‘CHRIS’ McINTOSH, 39

Christopher ‘Chris’ McIntosh, 39, who was caught with more than 27,000 child abuse material files also hoarded horrid Harry Potter, Ben 10 and Kim Possible fan fiction, investigators detected 3 million words within the stories which indicated child abuse material.

McIntosh was caught in possession of multiple devices including hard-drives, an iPhone and a laptop which contained a combined 27,584 child abuse material images, videos and documents when police searched his Southbank home in December 2020. He told police he downloaded the child abuse material over several years which he defined as “material which sexualises people under age of 16”.

The court was told McIntosh completed a community correction order and sex offender program for a 2010 conviction for child exploitation material offending.

McIntosh is on bail and will be sentenced at a later date.

To find more convicted offenders: www.offendersexposed.com.au

Source: https://www.heraldsun.com.au/leader/melbourne-city/southbank-nerd-dad-christopher-chris-mcintosh-pleads-guilty-to-possess-child-abuse-material/news-story/749bdfa323b25ba1b383a58b40c851d7

7/3/22
MUNNO PARA, SA
JOHN ROBERT NOWLAND, 37

John Robert Nowland, 37, who punched his partner in the head and told her to "run" before stabbing her three times in front of their children will spend at least three years behind bars for the "horrifying example of domestic violence".

Nowland pleaded guilty in the District Court to aggravated causing harm to his partner of 18 years.

Judge Jo-Anne Deuter sentenced Nowland to five years and nine months in prison with a non-parole period of three years and six months.

He has already served 14 months of that sentence.

www.offendersexposed.com

SOURCE: https://www.abc.net.au/news/2022-03-07/sa-john-robert-nowland-sentencing/100888358
